<div class="col-sm-7">

  <div class="form-group">
    <%= f.label :title, class: "sr-only" %>
    <%= f.text_area :title, class: "form-control input-lg flex-text", placeholder: "Title" %>
    <%= error_messages_for(@list, :title, "right") %>
  </div>

  <div class="form-group">
    <%= f.label :description, class: "sr-only" %>
    <%= f.text_area :description, class: "form-control input-lg description flex-text", placeholder: "Description (optional)" %>
  </div>

  <%= error_messages_for(@list, :items, "left") %>

  <div id="list">
    <<%= @list.ordered ? "o" : "u" %>l id="items">
      <%= f.fields_for :items do |item| %>
        <%= render 'item_fields', f: item %>
      <% end %>
      <div class="links" data-association-insertion-position="before" data-association-insertion-node="this">
        Type and hit ENTER, or <%= link_to_add_association "click here", f, :items %> <%= link_to "ü§î", "#", class: "js-form-help form-help-link", style: "text-decoration: none" %>
      </div>
    </<%= @list.ordered ? "o" : "u" %>l>
  </div>

  <div class="form-help" style="display:none">
    <h4 class="strikethrough">
      <span>Lil' Form Helper</span>
    </h4>
    <p>Navigating the list form ‚òùüèº is really fun with a couple keyboard shortcuts. Well, it's actually only sorta one shortcut, but it's got lots of features! Once you get the hang of it, you'll be listing lists with maximum efficiency.</p>
    <h4>TL;DR => <strong>Hit ENTER</strong> ü§ì</h4>
    <p>The best way to navigate between fields is by hitting ENTER:
    <ul>
      <li>Type your title, hit ENTER, and the cursor will move to Description.</li>
      <li>Type your Description, hit ENTER, and the cursor will move to the first Item.</li>
      <li>Type your Item, hit ENTER, a new item appears, and the cursor will move to it.</li>
      <li>And, if you hit ENTER in the last item field while it's empty, nothing happens!</li>
    </ul>
    <p>All of the above continues to work even after you've filled stuff out. So, let's say you need to edit the Title after creating a bunch items. Make your adjustments to the title and then just hit ENTER a bunch of times: the cursor will cruise right on through the Description and all existing items until it stops at the last empty item field.</p>
    <p><strong>TAB</strong></p>
    <p>Since ENTER is being so darn helpful around here, we decided to make tabbing between fields work a little differently by highlight all text in a field. But, don't worry, even when fully selected, hitting ENTER still moves the cursor along as expected.</p>
    <!-- TODO make this a link to our email address or contact form -->
    <p>Don't forget! If you've got feedback (good or bad), please send us an email.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="settings col-sm-5">
  <div class="section">
    <h4 class="strikethrough"><span>List Type</span></h4>
    <div class="options">
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :ordered, false, checked: true, class: "js-switch-list-type" %>
        <span>BULLETS</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :ordered, true, class: "js-switch-list-type" %>
        <span>NUMBERS</span>
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h4 class="strikethrough"><span>Comments</span></h4>
    <div class="options">
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :commenting, true, checked: true %>
        <span>ON</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :commenting, false %>
        <span>OFF</span>
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h4 class="strikethrough"><span>Status</span></h4>
    <div class="options">
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :public, true, checked: true %>
        <span>Public</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :public, false %>
        <span>Private</span>
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="status-help-text">Public lists are, as the name suggests, visible to the general public and search engine crawlers. Private lists are only visible to you when you are logged in. Status can be changed at anytime.</p>

  <div class="section">
    <%= f.submit "SAVE LIST", class: "btn btn-lg btn-block btn-lyl-primary" %>
  </div>

  <% if action_name == "edit" %>
    <div class="section">
      <%= link_to "DELETE LIST", @list, method: :delete, class: "btn btn-lg btn-block btn-lyl-delete", data: { confirm: "Are you sure you wanna delete this list? It will be gone forever and you can't undo this." } %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
